  "texts": [
    "So suppose that for some x, y ∈ A, x ∧ ♦ i y ̸ = ⊥.",
    "By definition of A L (Definition A.10), there are φ, ψ ∈ L(Φ, I) such that x = [φ] L and y = [ψ] L. (We will henceforth omit the subscripts for the equivalence classes.)",
    "Thus, x∧♦ i y ̸ = ⊥ implies ⊬ L φ → □ i ¬ψ.",
    "Assuming that L satisfies the finite existence lemma, it follows that there is a χ ∈ L(Φ, I) such that (i)⊬ L χ → ¬ψ and (ii) for all α ∈ L(Φ, I), if ⊢ L φ → □ i α, then ⊢ L χ → α.",
    "By (i), ψ ′ = ψ ∧ χ is L-consistent, so ⊥ ̸ = [ψ ′] ≤ [ψ]."
  ],
